<item>
            <title>[SUREFIRE-1695] Support multiple inheritance of @Categories</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SUREFIRE-1695</link>
                <project id="12317927" key="SUREFIRE">Maven Surefire (Moved to GitHub Issues)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We are using JUnit Categories together with Surefire&apos;s &amp;lt;includes&amp;gt;/&amp;lt;excludes&amp;gt; tags in a Test hierarchy. However we have observed some inconsistencies in the resolution.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Example:&#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;tt&gt;AbstractTest&lt;/tt&gt; is tagged with &lt;tt&gt;@Category(CategoryB.class)&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;tt&gt;TestA extends AbstractTest&lt;/tt&gt; and is tagged with &lt;tt&gt;@Category(CategoryA.class)&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;When running Surefire with &lt;tt&gt;&amp;lt;include&amp;gt;CategoryB&amp;lt;/include&lt;/tt&gt;&amp;gt;, TestA is not executed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There are a few more failure cases, written as (integration/unit) tests. I have provided a PR with a fix.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
